.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cleanroom
scans common macOS storage bloat locations and cleans rebuildable cache or
artifact data. It is dry-run by default and requires
.B --apply
before deleting files.
.PP
By default it does not delete browser profiles, saved password databases,
Keychains, Photos libraries, Mail, iCloud Drive, or arbitrary personal files.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B overview
Show a read-only storage dashboard with disk state, summaries, and next steps.
.TP
.B scan
Show disk usage, cleanup candidates, largest home folders, and large files.
.TP
.B system-data
Break common macOS System Data locations into review-only buckets with next commands.
.TP
.B plan
Rank safe cleanup opportunities and show copyable commands.
.TP
.B large
List large files for review without deleting anything.
.TP
.B duplicates
Find exact duplicate files for review without deleting anything.
.TP
.B documents
Rank top-level files and folders in ~/Documents or a provided directory with guard status.
.TP
.B desktop
Rank top-level files and folders on ~/Desktop with guard status.
.TP
.B screenshots
List screenshot and screen recording files for review without deleting anything.
.TP
.B archives
List archive and disk image files for review without deleting anything.
.TP
.B downloads
List old files in ~/Downloads for review without deleting anything.
.TP
.B installers
List old downloaded installer files in ~/Downloads for review.
.TP
.B nodes
List stale node_modules folders for review without deleting anything.
.TP
.B venvs
List stale Python virtualenv folders for review without deleting anything.
.TP
.B apps
List largest app bundles for review without uninstalling anything.
.TP
.B appdata
Rank large app support, container, group-container, HTTP storage, WebKit, and
saved-state folders with central guard status.
.TP
.B libraries
Inventory protected media and creative libraries such as Photos, Music, TV,
iMovie, GarageBand, and Logic without deleting anything.
.TP
.B cloud
Inventory protected cloud-sync folders such as iCloud Drive, CloudStorage,
Dropbox, Google Drive, OneDrive, Box, and Sync without deleting anything.
.TP
.B personal
Inventory protected Mail, Messages, Contacts, Calendars, Notes, Reminders,
Voice Memos, and call-history data without deleting anything.
.TP
.B browsers
Inventory browser profile and cache footprint without deleting profiles,
passwords, cookies, bookmarks, sessions, or settings.
.TP
.B leftovers
Find app or vendor leftovers in common support, cache, preference, container,
WebKit, log, and launch-item locations. Plain mode previews. Applied cleanup
requires
.B --trash
so matches are recoverable through the normal apply log and restore flow.
.TP
.B backups
Inventory local iPhone and iPad backups for review without deleting them.
.TP
.B xcode
Inventory Xcode build, archive, DeviceSupport, and simulator storage.
.TP
.B android
Inventory Android SDK, NDK, system image, emulator, AVD, platform, build-tool,
command-line tool, and Android Studio cache storage with safety labels.
.TP
.B startup
List LaunchAgents and LaunchDaemons for review without unloading or removing anything.
.TP
.B trash
Inventory current user Trash contents without emptying Trash.
.TP
.B caches
Inventory safe and opt-in cache buckets with preview/apply commands.
.TP
.B diagnostics
Inventory user logs, diagnostic reports, and CrashReporter data.
.TP
.B packages
Inventory package-manager caches and stores with preview/apply commands.
.TP
.B homebrew
Inventory Homebrew cache, logs, Cellar, Caskroom, and service/runtime folders.
.TP
.B toolchains
Inventory language and toolchain caches such as Go, pip, uv, SwiftPM, Maven,
Composer, RubyGems, and Bundler.
.TP
.B containers
Inventory local container VM disks and image stores for Docker Desktop, Colima,
Lima, and Podman. Cleanup is high-impact and opt-in.
.TP
.B snapshots
List local Time Machine snapshots for review.
.TP
.B report
Generate a Markdown cleanup report.
.TP
.B clean
Preview or apply cleanup.
.TP
.B history
List recent apply logs.
.TP
.B restore
Restore files moved by --trash from an apply log. Dry-run by default.
.TP
.B rules
List cleanup rules, safety level, opt-in flag, and affected paths.
.TP
.B interactive
Prompt for cleanup categories and then run the same clean flow.
.TP
.B doctor
Check platform, dependencies, disk state, and protected data assumptions.
.TP
.B protect
Audit protected personal data and app profile paths that cleanroom will not
remove wholesale.
.TP
.B guard
Explain whether specific paths are removable by cleanroom's central safety guard.
.TP
.B categories
Explain cleanup categories and safety levels.
.TP
.B init-config
Write a starter config file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --apply
Actually delete selected files.
.TP
.B --trash
Move cleanroom-managed path removals to ~/.Trash/cleanroom-* instead of
deleting them immediately.
.TP
.B --log " path"
Write the apply audit log to a specific file.
.TP
.B --limit " n"
Number of history entries or large files to show.
.TP
.B --min-mb " n"
Minimum file size for large and duplicate review commands. Defaults to 500.
.TP
.B --yes
Skip confirmation prompts.
.TP
.B --preset " safe|dev|deep"
Enable a group of cleanup categories.
.TP
.B --config " path"
Load a config file.
.TP
.B --exclude " path"
Protect a path from deletion.
.TP
.B --include-app-caches
Remove nested app cache folders only.
.TP
.B --include-dev-heavy
Remove heavy developer artifacts such as SDK components and simulator state.
.TP
.B --include-ai-workspaces
Remove generated AI-agent workspace data.
.TP
.B --include-ai-models
Remove downloaded local AI model stores.
.TP
.B --include-containers
Remove local container VM disks and image stores. This can remove containers,
images, and volumes.
.TP
.B --include-diagnostics
Remove old user diagnostic reports and CrashReporter files older than
.BR --days .
.TP
.B --include-user-trash
Empty ~/.Trash during apply. This is irreversible.
.TP
.B --include-installers
Remove old downloaded installer files from ~/Downloads during apply.
.TP
.B --include-venv-stale
Remove stale Python virtualenv folders older than
.BR --days
when they contain pyvenv.cfg.
